goals.question: What is the average yield of barley across all sites?
goals.rationale: A box plot will show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the yield distribution, giving a good idea of the central tendency and spread of the data.

goals.question: How does the yield vary across different varieties of barley?
goals.visualization: Grouped bar chart of yield by variety
goals.rationale: A grouped bar chart will allow us to compare the yield of different varieties of barley side-by-side, making it easy to identify which varieties have the highest and lowest yields.

goals.question: What is the relationship between yield and nitrogen level?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of yield vs nitrogen level
goals.rationale: A scatter plot will show the relationship between yield and nitrogen level, allowing us to see if there is a positive or negative correlation between the two variables.

goals.question: How does the yield vary across different sites?
goals.visualization: Stacked bar chart of yield by site
goals.rationale: A stacked bar chart will allow us to compare the yield of different sites, as well as see the contribution of each variety to the total yield at each site.

goals.question: What is the distribution of yield across all sites?
goals.rationale: A histogram will show the frequency distribution of yield, allowing us to see if the data is normally distributed or skewed, and identify any outliers.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='site', y='yield', data=data)
    ax.set_title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Site')
    ax.set_ylabel('Yield')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Site', loc='upper right', labels=data['site'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
